olume offers highly readable and wide-ranging essays on Grünbein’s substantial œuvre, complemented by specially commissioned material and an interview with the poet. It covers the German and European traditions, and engages with Grünbein’s works in the context of a number of relevant topics, such as ‘memory’, ‘urban life’, ‘mortality’, ‘love’, and ‘presence’; it also probes Grünbein’s sustained dialogue with the natural sciences and the visual arts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aGrünbein, Durs. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aDurs Grünbein.1 aCooper, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEskin, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEskin, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrünbein, Durs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Sonja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeeder, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeeder, Karen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOwen, Ruth J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRegier, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReumkens, Noël, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVendler, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWebber, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWerner, Lukas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Christopher, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTit